        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-06-22 12:48:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-2\n\nThe features pom.xml itself should have the repo's pom.xml as its parent - not features-parent.  What we really should do is create a new project parent (like rootpom/pom.xml) whose parent is feature-parent vs odlparent.  I'm asking to move the rootpom from sdnc/core to a separate repo (sdnc/parent) to resolve current circular dependency.  Once that is created, we'll have multiple parent poms defined in that new project so that projects that build features can use features-parent as ancestor.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
